Q1. - HTML formatting tags 
<b>
<strong>
<i>
<em> 
<mark>
<small>

Q2. - 
use the rowspan attribute to merge rows and the colspan attribute to merge columns. 
code - 
<html>
<head>
    <title></title>
</head>
<body>
    <table border="1">
        <tr>
            <th>Header 1</th>
            <th>Header 2</th>
            <th>Header 3</th>
            <th>Header 4</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td rowspan="2" colspan="2">Merged Cell</td>
            <td>Cell 3</td>
            <td>Cell 4</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Cell 7</td>
            <td>Cell 8</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Cell 9</td>
            <td>Cell 10</td>
            <td>Cell 11</td>
            <td>Cell 12</td>
        </tr>
    </table>
</body>
</html>


Q3. - 
cellspacing controls the space between cells, while cellpadding controls the space inside the cells.

Q4. - 
Sementic elements provide better structure and accessibility.
example - <header>
<nav>
<section>
<footer>
<main>

Q5. - 
<html>
<head>
    <title></title>
    <style>
        body {
            background-image: url('background.jpg');
            background-size: cover;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Welcome to My Webpage</h1>
    <p>This page has a background image.</p>
</body>
</html>


Q6. - 
The alt attribute specifies an alternate text for an area, if the image cannot be displayed.
